question: What is the code of the device with the udi code (01)13118397031411(11)230218(17)480304(10)23619409(21)26944176764252519?
answers:
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>
PREFIX syn: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#>
PREFIX udi: <https://knacc.umbc.edu/dae-young/kim/ontologies/synthea#fda:UDI>
PREFIX pl: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#PlainLiteral>
SELECT DISTINCT ?code
WHERE {
?device a syn:Device ;
syn:udi ?udi .
BIND(STR((SUBSTR(?udi,3,3) )) AS ?udi_cut1)
BIND(STR((SUBSTR(?udi,7,2) )) AS ?udi_cut2)
BIND(STR((SUBSTR(?udi,10,2) )) AS ?udi_cut3)
BIND(STR((SUBSTR(?udi,13,7) )) AS ?udi_cut4)
BIND(STR((SUBSTR(?udi,21,11) )) AS ?udi_cut5)
BIND(STR((SUBSTR(?udi,33,19) )) AS ?udi_cut6)
FILTER (?udi_cut1 = '01')
FILTER (?udi_cut2 = '13')
FILTER (?udi_cut3 = '11')
FILTER (?udi_cut4 = '23')
FILTER (?udi_cut5 = '26')
FILTER (?udi_cut6 = '480304')
?device syn:code ?code
}
